Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] winepulse/mmdevapi: Avoid the blocking delta hotplug
 path.

The original DS5 hotplug patch used a PulseAudio subscription callback and a
blocking delta query path. That is fragile when multiple processes in the same
prefix use audio at the same time, because one mmdevapi update thread can block
inside the driver while another process owns the PulseAudio state transitions.

Keep the wine-staging PulseAudio initialization path and make the DS5 endpoint
query opt out of blocking delta updates. This preserves the device metadata and
endpoint snapshot support needed by the DS5 haptic patches without starting the
fragile background hotplug updater.
diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 91a84b115f2..42b9aa2f548 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1279,7 +1279,7 @@ void create_update_thread(void)
         ERR("CreateThread failed: %lu\n", GetLastError());
         g_update_thread_running = FALSE;
     } else
-        SetThreadPriority(update_thread_proc, THREAD_PRIORITY_BELOW_NORMAL);
+        SetThreadPriority(g_update_thread, THREAD_PRIORITY_BELOW_NORMAL);
 
     LeaveCriticalSection(&device_list_cs);
 }
